\begin{align*}
\|\mathbf{p}\|^2 &= \|\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{p}\|^2 \\
&= \|\mathbf{a}\|^2 - 2 \mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{p} + \|\mathbf{p}\|^2 \\
&= 3d^2 - 2 \mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{p}.
\end{align*}Similarly,
\begin{align*}
\|\mathbf{q}\|^2 &= 3d^2 - 2 \mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{q}.
\end{align*}Also,
\begin{align*}
\|\mathbf{p} - \mathbf{q}\|^2 &= \|\mathbf{p}\|^2 + \|\mathbf{q}\|^2 - 2 \mathbf{p} \cdot \mathbf{q} \\
&= 6d^2 - 2 (\mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{p} + \mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{q} + \mathbf{p} \cdot \mathbf{q}).
\end{align*}Since $PA = PB = PC,$ the centroid $G$ of triangle $ABC$ is the circumcenter of triangle $PAB.$  Therefore, $\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{p}$ is orthogonal to $\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{p}$ and $\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{p}.$  Hence,
\[\mathbf{a} \cdot (\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{p}) = \mathbf{p} \cdot (\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{p}) = 0.\]Then
\begin{align*}
\|\mathbf{p} - \mathbf{a}\|^2 &= \|\mathbf{p}\|^2 + \|\mathbf{a}\|^2 - 2 \mathbf{p} \cdot \mathbf{a} \\
&= 6d^2 - 2 \mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{p} \\
&= 3d^2 + \|\mathbf{p}\|^2,
\end{align*}so $\|\mathbf{p} - \mathbf{a}\| = \sqrt{3} d.$  Similarly, $\|\mathbf{q} - \mathbf{a}\| = \sqrt{3} d.$

Since the planes of triangles $PAB$ and $QAB$ form a $120^\circ$ dihedral angle, $\angle PAQ = 120^\circ.$  Then from the Law of Cosines on triangle $PAQ,$
\[\|\mathbf{p} - \mathbf{q}\| = \sqrt{3} d.\]Hence,
\[6d^2 - 2 (\mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{p} + \mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{q} + \mathbf{p} \cdot \mathbf{q}) = 3d^2.\]Since $\mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{p} = \mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{q},$
\[6d^2 - 4 \mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{p} - 2 \mathbf{p} \cdot \mathbf{q} = 3d^2.\]Since $\|\mathbf{p} - \mathbf{a}\| = \|\mathbf{q} - \mathbf{a}\| = \sqrt{3} d,$
\[6d^2 - 4 \cdot 300 d^2 \cos \theta - 2 (\sqrt{3} d)^2 = 3d^2,\]where $\theta$ is the angle between $\mathbf{p}$ and $\mathbf{q}.$  Solving for $d$ gives $d = \boxed{300 \sqrt{2}}.$

