We have that $AH_A = BH_B = CH_C = 200$, so $O'$ is the orthocenter of $\triangle H_AH_BH_C$. Let $O''$ be the circumcenter of $\triangle H_AH_BH_C$. Then $O''$ is equidistant from $H_A$, $H_B$, and $H_C$, so $d(O'',H_A) = d(O'',H_B) = d(O'',H_C) = 200$. Thus, $d(O'',O') = 200\sqrt{3} - 200 = 200(\sqrt{3} - 1)$.

Let $\theta$ be the angle between $\overrightarrow{PA}$ and $\overrightarrow{QA}$. Then $\angle POQ = 180^\circ - \theta$, so by the Law of Cosines on $\triangle POQ$, we have
\[d^2 = PQ^2 + 4 \cdot PQ \cdot d(O'',O') + 4d(O'',O')^2 - 2PQ \cdot d(O'',O') \cos \theta.\]We have $PQ = 2d(O',O'') = 400(\sqrt{3} - 1)$, so
